# ============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT NOTES
# ============================================================================

# 1. Backend Configuration:
#    - Copy backend/.env.example to backend/.env
#    - Configure DATABASE_URL (Neon PostgreSQL connection string)
#    - Set JWT_SECRET (min 32 characters, use: openssl rand -base64 32)
#    - Set ALLOWED_ORIGINS for CORS

# 2. Frontend Configuration:
#    - Copy frontend/.env.local.example to frontend/.env.local
#    - Set NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL (backend API URL, default: http://localhost:8000)
#    - Set BETTER_AUTH_SECRET (must match backend JWT_SECRET)

# 3. Security:
#    - NEVER commit .env files to version control
#    - Use strong, randomly generated secrets
#    - Rotate secrets regularly in production

# 4. Quick Start:
#    docker-compose up --build
